article.headline: Western Michigan 82, Eastern Michigan 71
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. (AP) -- Ben Reed scored 21 points for the second consecutive game and had a game-high 11 rebounds to lead Western Michigan to an 82-71 victory over Eastern Michigan on Thursday night. Reed was 9-of-16 as the Broncos (15-6, 8-3 Mid-American) retained sole possession of first place in the MAC West. Rickey Willis added 16 points for the team, Levi Rost scored 14 and Stane's Bufford had 12. Rost had a game-high six assists. Markus Austin scored 21 to lead Eastern Michigan (9-11, 3-8), which lost its seventh straight. John Bowler and Darryl Garrett chipped in 15 apiece for the Eagles. Eastern hit 52.4 percent of its shots in the second half, when it was outscored 42-34 by Western, but was outrebounded 17-11 and committed 11 turnovers. Western erased a two-point Eastern lead on a 3-point basket by Reed with 10:56 left in the first half that sparked an 11-0 run to put the Broncos ahead 26-17. Eastern never led after that as Western built its advantage to as many as 14 points in the second half. The Broncos outrebounded Eastern Michigan 40-28 for the game.
